name: Black Eye
explorationReport: One explorer went insane but no civilisations were found

name: Andromeda
explorationReport: Our closest neighbour though we were too late to get to know them

name: Milky Way
explorationReport: The cradle of humanity, well-explored

name: Andromeda Prime
explorationReport: It's vast water supply beneath the ice seemed promising, yet no life was found underneath it

name: Centaurus Spiral
explorationReport: Craters on some planets show signs of a impact but our scientists were unable to find out if this was alien-made or purely a coincidence

name: Draco's Wisp
explorationReport: While a great source for our gas reserves, no signs of life were found here

name: Pegasus Cluster
explorationReport: When we made contact, our lead explorer told us the sentient gas cloud seemed smug. We're not sure how but we think he's right.

name: Triangulum Void
explorationReport: Be careful you do not gaze upon this galaxy for too long

name: Sagittarius Nebula
explorationReport: Most of the oceans we found were boiling hot, too hot for life

name: Virgo Zenith
explorationReport: No life was found among the craters and the lava streams

name: Perseus Chain
explorationReport: While promising, we did not find any avian friends

name: Phoenix Arm
explorationReport: No life has risen in the Phoenix system

name: Hydra Swarm
explorationReport: Despite its frightening name, no monsters were found here

name: Lyra Lens
explorationReport: Our explorers complained about the long trip with little results

name: Auriga Disk
explorationReport: Most orbits are too unstable to ever support life, even with terraforming

name: Orion Rift
explorationReport: Why our scientists thought there might be aquaphibians in this Chtonian wasteland is the real mystery

name: Cygnus Drift
explorationReport: One exploration cruiser got pulled into a gas giant, this place holds only death, no life

name: Taurus Spire
explorationReport: Its scorching stars ruined any chance of life

name: Canis Majoris Stream
explorationReport: No life was found inbetween these dog stars

name: Ursa Minor Swirl
explorationReport: Our explorers found many breathtaking views but little to no sentient life

name: Cetus Arc
explorationReport: Our explorers had to return prematurely due to losing several men to frostbite. They doubt however that they could have ever found sentient life here.

name: Carina Depth
explorationReport: While no life was found here, our lead explorer has suggested terraforming a planet to build a beach resort here.

name: Pavo Halo
explorationReport: It would have been a reach to find sentient life here

name: Lepus Loop
explorationReport: ...our lead explore said last time, we're stuck in a time loop. Which really annoys me because that what...

name: Monoceros Fracture
explorationReport: While no life was found, the strange orbits of the stars continue to intrigue our scientists

name: Ophiuchus Veil
explorationReport: One explorer found a planet made entirely out of gold, ever since he refuses to return to our Capital planet

name: Aquarius Filament
explorationReport: Explorers were shocked to find no life here

name: Cassiopeia Lightyear
explorationReport: What few planets there are, are too small and too hot to support life

name: Kronos Spiral
explorationReport: The curious nebulas here earned a photographer quite a few prizes. Unfortunately no life was found

name: Promethean Halo
explorationReport: The ocean worlds are silent

name: Titania's Veil
explorationReport: No message came from beyond the veil

name: Pandora's Lens
explorationReport: One troublesome explorer kept reporting about a box, unfortunately no such reports occurred about life

name: Hyperion Crest
explorationReport: No life was found here

name: Nyx's Whisper
explorationReport: Not even the whispers of life were heard in this desolate system

name: Aetherium Shard
explorationReport: Its precious metal troves intrigue us but no life was found here

name: Gaia's Mirror
explorationReport: They are new to the spacefaring age yet their predictive technologies already rival ours

name: Persephone's Arc
explorationReport: Made more out of energy than gas, these beings continue to surprise our scientists

name: Eos Belt
explorationReport: The belt of dwarf planets is void of life

name: Thanatos Rift
explorationReport: Despite its mythological reference, we do not think there was every anybody alive to die here

name: Zeus Ascension
explorationReport: Zeus has no pantheon to rule over among these stars:

name: Hades' Passage
explorationReport: The arrival of our explorers was met with great jubilation, followed by disappointment, as if they were suspecting someone else?

name: Echoing Chaos
explorationReport: The only echos to be heard here were the cries of frustrated explorers

name: Styx's Horizon
explorationReport: They watched us with suspicion as our more advanced vessel met theirs on a neighbouring moon

name: Olympus Nebula
explorationReport: Mount Olympus is as devoid of life here as it was on Mars

name: Callisto Cluster
explorationReport: No life was found here

name: Maia's Light
explorationReport: Maia's Light has only shone on our explorers

name: Zorathian Spire
explorationReport: Their likeness to terrestial octopodes baffled our explorers

name: Klynos Vortex
explorationReport: A classified accident involving black holes happened here, nothing further to report

name: Vyr'dal Spiral
explorationReport: This system would have made a good neighbour if any life had been found here

name: Xephar Flux
explorationReport: This civilisation vanished after activating a mysterious engine, our scientists will be busy investigating their doom

name: Kryzann Lattice
explorationReport: Despite its picturesque auroras, this planet hides no secret but its own emptiness

name: Drakan Prime
explorationReport: One planet was shrouded in eternal twilight, but the shadows hid no secrets of sentient life.

name: Sythal Enclave
explorationReport: Not even the spores of microbial life could survive the poisonous atmospheres we found here

name: Lyn'xara Drift
explorationReport: The planets danced in chaotic spirals, but no sentient beings were found to watch the show

name: Vortar Expanse
explorationReport: Our explorers searched far and wide and found nothing

name: Zypherion Net
explorationReport: Scientist continue to debate who gave the system this name and who is Zypherion but rumours of alien interference were unfortunately dispelled

name: Kyron Eclipse
explorationReport: Surprisingly this system does not have more eclipses as our own Milky Way, unsurprisingly it also holds no intelligent life

name: Vextris Nova
explorationReport: One explorer fleet almost crashed into a wandering planet

name: Large Magellanic Cloud
explorationReport: Our geologists were overjoyed by the many unique ores and formations, our biologists remained disappointed

name: Bode's Galaxy
explorationReport: The explorers marveled at the system's gravity wells but left disappointed, as no life clung to their pull.

name: Carafe
explorationReport: No life and a surprising lack of glass as well

name: Hoag's Object
explorationReport: The late Arthur Hoag will be disappointed to find out there was no life to be found in his namesake

name: Bear Paw Galaxy
explorationReport: Any jokes about alien bears were quickly dispelled

name: Twin Butterflies
explorationReport: One explorer cried due to a beautiful cosmic cloud, all cried due to the lack of life

name: Circinus Galaxy
explorationReport: This system whispered promises of life, but our sensors only found barren rocks and lifeless seas.

name: Eye of Sauron
explorationReport: We walked into easily and found no resistance

name: Fireworks Galaxy
explorationReport: It seems like a precursor species has given them cybernetics, how intriguing!

name: Pillars of Eternity
explorationReport: Our explorers were eager to meet the great civilisation that lives around these pillars and were greated with much decorum

name: Godzilla Galaxy
explorationReport: No life was found here, perhaps for the best

name: Lindsay-Shapley Ring
explorationReport: Exploration missions confirm the fact that this galaxy was created by a collision

name: Malin 1
explorationReport: No life was found here, time to search for Malin 2?

name: Mayala
explorationReport: Not even a hivemind could survive in this scorching galaxy

name: Vanhini Galaxy
explorationReport: No life was found here but you can always receive a hint by calling Stijn 'Verdost'

name: Starfish Arms
explorationReport: This galaxy remains a beautiful vista with no inhabitants

name: Whirlpool Vortex
explorationReport: Their aggression indicates they want to be left alone, their strength and size makes us honour that wish

name: Verdost Cloud
explorationReport: No life was found here but you can always receive a hint by calling Nicolas 'Vanhini'

name: Altair Spiral
explorationReport: Several planets were found cracked in pieces, a sign of a great calamity

name: Betelgeuse Swarm
explorationReport: No life showed up, even after repeating the name thrice

name: Rigel Cluster
explorationReport: One planet looked a lot like Earth, except for it being totally empty

name: Capella Disk
explorationReport: Many planets here proved to be radioactive, which was not beneficial for the development of life

name: Sirius Void
explorationReport: Baffled our explorers returned home from these dog stars

name: Antares Halo
explorationReport: We didnâ€™t find life, but the team enjoyed naming the weirdly shaped asteroids

name: Procyon Arc
explorationReport: Several planets here were compared to a sauna, too hot for any life to ever appear

name: Vega Rift
explorationReport: Our explorers detected a suspicious wandering object in this system but were unable to find it, we shall conclude there is no life here, right?

name: Arcturus Filament
explorationReport: The planets of this system either had too much sunshine or way too little

name: Deneb Lattice
explorationReport: If there was life here, they left a long time ago. Maybe they knew something our explorers didn't.

name: Fomalhaut Stream
explorationReport: We're not sure how they knew of the gesture, but when we made first contact, one of their drone units hugged our explorer

name: Polaris Cascade
explorationReport: The lead scientist described it as 'empty but pretty.'

name: Aldebaran Nebula
explorationReport: We had high expectations but all that we detected were our own explorers

name: Canopus Lens
explorationReport: We scanned every inch of a particularly promising planet, all it resulted in was a lot of time wasted

name: Spica Array
explorationReport: We started to number the lifeless planets starting from zero, it seemed fitting enough

name: Mira Swirl
explorationReport: Endless storms battered the explorers' landing craft, forcing an early departure and no discoveries

name: Bellatrix Bridge
explorationReport: Despite its name, no structures were ever built here

name: Thuban Fringe
explorationReport: They met us with great enthousiasm, taking our explorers on great tours of the virtual worlds they have constructed

name: Algol Cluster
explorationReport: The celestial storms are mesmerizing but would tear any form of life apart in moments.

name: Zubenelgenubi Disk
explorationReport: Our lead explorer is considering a colony here nevertheless, if only for the catchy name

name: Achernar Arm
explorationReport: A forest of crystal spires glistened under twin suns, but no creatures stirred among them.

name: Alnilam Stretch
explorationReport: It seems like this so called 'Dominion' destroyed itself in a great war

name: Mintaka Arch
explorationReport: When our fleet arrived, we were greeted by a grand armada which we had never seen before

name: Saiph Verge
explorationReport: These oceans are swarming with life, a truely majestic sight
